release_note: Thanks to your feedback we are continually improving the app. This time we are introducing a new interactive mindfulness exercise in the form of a video in all our courses. Additionally this update includes some minor bug fixes and performance improvements for you.

The aim of this update is to simplify the introduction to the product and provide an overview of the course content through high quality videos. Additionally you now have a streamlined version for providing prescriber information if you want to extend your course or add a new course. In addition we have carefully fixed bugs in the app to further optimize your user experience and make it even smoother.

This update contains a revised version of the instructions for use to make the product easier to use. In addition the provision of prescriber information has been optimized and further bug fixes have been made.

With this update we make it easier for you to convert your recipe into an activation code. You can upload your recipe at www.selfapy.com rezeptservice. We will then help you submit it to your health insurance company and they will send you your activation code after about 10 days. In the meantime you can start using the launcher and use features like the diary. We ll explain to you in a short video how to get from the start program to your course.

New function in your Selfapy app: From now on you can view all of your including past Selfapy courses in the app and access the content. A clear profile for all your Selfapy courses: depression generalized anxiety disorder panic disorder stress. Easily extend and activate new courses from your profile.
New courses are available: Binge Eating and Bulimia.

Is your course running out soon No problem at all: With this release you can extend the duration of your course in the app with just a few clicks. All you need is a new activation code from your health insurance company.
Bug fixes
